{
  "texts": [
    "With 3D landmarks and camera pose that illustrate the 3D orientation in which the 2D radiograph is taken, models can more accurately locate the 2D position of landmarks on any designated radiograph of that same 3D volume.Method proposed in Suh et al.",
    "2023 8 uses a U-Net 9 structure to detect landmarks, which treat the landmarking problem as a semantic segmentation task.",
    "In this work, a probability map is generated from the trained U-Net, and landmarks are extracted based on the maximum probability of a landmark being located at a particular pixel location.",
    "While this approach has been proven effective for segmentation tasks in other fields, it is limited in precisely locating landmarks.",
    "Existing training methods adopt pixel-wise cross-entropy loss between the output probability maps and ground truth masks."
  ]
}